<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-12-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-12-19T23:40:00-05:00" n="368" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1905-12-27T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1905-12-20T00:00:00-04:40">undated</date>]. [<hi rend="italic">Received December 27,
                            1905</hi>].</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Have received letter of President dated the 24th, saying that he is about
                            to absent himself from capital in order to reestablish legal procedure,
                            and later on will declare another city temporary capital, and will then
                            name a new Cabinet. He is reported to be 15 miles west, fighting troops
                            sent by Cabinet. American citizens interior alarmed, fearing that
                            landing American seamen would be followed by violence to themselves.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>